request.description:
### POST /invitations

This endpoint is used to send invitations via HTTP POST request. This endpoint send email to complete registration (users).

_(Only for admin user)_

#### Request

The request should be made to {{url}}/invitations with a payload in x-www-form-urlencoded format. The payload should include the following parameter:

- `email` (text): The email address of the recipient.


#### Response

Upon a successful request, the API returns a response with a status code of 201 and a JSON object in the following format:

``` json
{
  "data": {
    "email": "",
    "token": "",
    "isActive": null,
    "expiresAt": ""
  }
}

 ```

The response JSON schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "email": { "type": "string" },
        "token": { "type": "string" },
        "isActive": { "type": ["boolean", "null"] },
        "expiresAt": { "type": "string" }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

